{
  "text": "If the powder diffraction pattern is obtained with care, and can be rigorously normalized such that the normalized scattering function S(Q) can be obtained, then these data can be transformed to give the pair distribution function (PDF), which is able to give insight into local ordering in materials (Proffen & Billinge, 1999; Proffen et al., 2002; [CITATION_1] Billinge & Kanatzidis, 2004; [CITATION_2] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "117125713",
